Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.004
LCD TV BRAVIA with Android TV function
2015 model
Video tutorial for initial setup
The screen images may differ depending on your TV model and the situation.

00:00:04.004 --> 00:00:10.010
This tutorial guides you to sign in to Google™ with your account during setup. Prepare your Google™ account before you start setup.
※ You can go to the next step without signing in to Google™ by selecting [ skip ].

00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:16.884
After installing the TV and connecting antenna cables to the TV, press POWER on the TV.
※ Terminal arrangement may vary depending on the model.

00:00:16.884 --> 00:00:27.060
Please wait several minutes until the TV starts up.

00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:45.212
Insert batteries into the Touchpad Remote Control, then press the touchpad.
※ Button arrangement and functions of the remote may vary depending on your region/country.

00:00:45.212 --> 00:00:51.585
※ You can set up the Touchpad Remote Control after the initial setup.

00:00:51.585 --> 00:00:54.621
We are going to explain how to use the IR (infrared) Remote Control.

00:00:54.621 --> 00:01:18.812
Insert batteries into the IR Remote Control, point this remote to the optical receiver of the TV.
※ Button arrangement and functions of the remote may vary depending on your region/country.

00:01:18.812 --> 00:01:27.187
Select a language and press [ + ] button.

00:01:27.187 --> 00:01:31.425
Select your Wi-Fi network.
※ When the TV is connected to a network using a LAN cable, this step is not displayed.

00:01:31.425 --> 00:01:36.263
This tutorial explains how to connect to the Internet using a wireless LAN router which supports WPS.

00:01:36.263 --> 00:01:43.470
Select [ CONNECT VIA WPS ].
※ If you set up this step later, select [ SKIP ]. 

00:01:43.470 --> 00:01:53.180
Press the [ WPS ] or [ AOSS ] button on your router.

00:01:55.349 --> 00:02:01.722
Please wait a moment while [ Connecting to Google ] is displayed.

00:02:01.722 --> 00:02:06.093
Sign in to Google™ using your Google™ account.

00:02:06.093 --> 00:02:11.231
We are going to explain how to sign in to Google™ by using your email address and password of Google™ account.

00:02:11.231 --> 00:02:20.674
Select [ USE YOUR PASSWORD ].
※ If you set up this step later, select [ SKIP ].
※ Words may differ from the actual contents. 

00:02:20.674 --> 00:02:26.346
Enter your Google™ account email address except @ and the succeeding characters.

00:02:26.346 --> 00:02:31.652
After entering, select [ NEXT ].

00:02:31.652 --> 00:02:37.958
Enter your Google™ account password.

00:02:37.958 --> 00:02:43.530
After entering, select [ NEXT ].

00:02:45.632 --> 00:02:57.778
View and read [ TERMS OF SERVICE ] and [ PRIVACY POLICY ] of Google™.

00:02:57.778 --> 00:03:07.220
If the TV is not connected to the Internet, the URL will be displayed instead of [ TERMS OF SERVICE ] and [ PRIVACY POLICY ] of Google™.
Confirm the contents of the URL by accessing from other connected devices.

00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:14.361
Select [ CONTINUE ]. 

00:03:14.361 --> 00:03:18.231
Decide whether you give Google™ and third party apps your permission to use your device's location.

00:03:18.231 --> 00:03:23.236
By selecting [ YES ], you can use Google™ apps and third-party apps conveniently.

00:03:23.236 --> 00:03:27.874
Select [ YES ] or [ NO ].

00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:35.015
Select region and area.

00:03:35.015 --> 00:03:41.655
Press ↓ button to read the full text.

00:03:41.655 --> 00:03:48.528
Confirm the contents and select [ AGREE ] or [ DISAGREE ].

00:03:48.528 --> 00:03:59.506
Select [ ON ] or [ OFF ] about Automatic software download.

00:03:59.506 --> 00:04:05.645
Connect the antenna cables firmly before you choose the broadcast type for channel search.

00:04:05.645 --> 00:04:09.583
Please wait until the channel search ends.

00:04:10.117 --> 00:04:14.087
Optimize the direction of outputting the TV speaker sound. 

00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:19.793
Select [ TABLE-TOP STAND ] or [ WALL MOUNT ] specifying how your TV is positioned.

00:04:19.793 --> 00:04:25.866
If you often display videos on the TV from mobile apps, such as YouTube, select [ ON ] about Remote start. 
You can control your TV from your mobile device conveniently.
※ When the TV is connected to a network using a LAN cable, this step is not displayed.

00:04:25.866 --> 00:04:31.938
The picture is displayed on the TV by pressing button on the screen of your mobile device during the playback of the video.

00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:35.475
Select [ ON ] or [ OFF ].

00:04:35.475 --> 00:04:40.447
Select [ COMPLETE ].

00:04:41.481 --> 00:04:45.252
Setup has completed, the Home Menu is displayed.

00:04:45.252 --> 00:04:50.157
This TV provides the help guide.

00:04:50.157 --> 00:05:01.401
For further information, refer to this help guide.

00:05:01.401 --> 00:05:07.440
We hope you will enjoy using Sony's Android TV.

